<author><name><![CDATA[AbuKhuzaimahAnsari]]></name></author>
<updated>2017-03-09T21:11:40+01:00</updated>
<published>2017-03-09T21:11:40+01:00</published>
<id>https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=963&amp;p=1338#p1338</id>
<link href="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=963&amp;p=1338#p1338"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: 999 Statements In Defence of the Salafi Creed and Manhaj]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=963&amp;p=1338#p1338"><![CDATA[
<strong>999 Statements In Defence of the Salafi Creed and Manhaj<br /><br />-15-</strong><br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />Imam Ali ibn al-Madini [234H] said in explanation of the hadith of a group of my ummah always remain upon the truth... &quot;They are the people of hadith&quot; [Jame Tirmidhi 2:43]<br /></div></blockquote><br /><br /><strong>BENEFITS</strong><br /><br />1. The Ahlul Hadith are upon the truth and the truth is with them.<br /><br />2. The Ahlul Hadith were around in the 3rd Islamic century. Way before the deobandis, Barelvis, Asharis and Maturidis were around.<br /><br />3. Only the foolish and out right ignorant denies the existence of the Ahlul Hadith<br /><br />4. The madhabs were not even formulated when the school or madhab of Ahlul Hadith was around.<br /><br />5. We should aim and strive to follow the way of Ahlul Hadith as the truth is with them Insha Allah.<br /><br /><br /><span style="color: #0000BF">www.salafiri.com</span><br /><span style="color: #BF8000">www.forum.salafiri.com  </span>    <br /><span style="color: #FF0000">www.salafiri.bigcartel.com</span><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://twitter.com/salafiri_com">http://twitter.com/salafiri_com</a><!-- m --><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.facebook.com/Salafiri">https://www.facebook.com/Salafiri</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=48">AbuKhuzaimahAnsari</a> — Thu Mar 09, 2017 8:11 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
